title: Harry P. Leu Gardens
text: Harry P. Len Gardens is 50 acres, a museum and Botanical. Facilities, Covid 19 procedures, everything labeled. Walking trails, benches, birds, wildlife : squirrels, rabbits.

title: Lion Country Safari
text: Lion Country Safari just a wonderful experience, they have a great staff. They operate under CDC and Covid 19 procedures. We totally disagree with the Gov. DeSantis lifting masks restrictions. The park has many animals, but the star this week was not the lions, elephants, rhinos, it was a brand new just born baby zebra.

title: Lake Griffin State Park
text: Lake Griffin State Park is in full bloom, they have great facilities, birds, wildlife. They have lots of things to do.

title: DeLeon Springs State Park
text: DeLeon Springs State Park is wonderful, great staff, Covid 19 procedures, facilities. Lots of things to do, swimming, snorkeling, birds, wildlife. The Sugar Mill is super restaurant.

title: Sikorski's Deli
text: Sikorski's Deli is using Covid 19 procedures, parking. a very good staff. I enjoyed the polish deli part of the menu.

title: Florida Botanical Gardens
text: Florida Botanical Gardens is keeping with Covid 19 procedures, they have a very good staff, facilities. Its spring and this place is beautiful. They have plants, birds and wildlife.

title: Hawkers Asian Street Food
text: Hawkers has a casual decor with tables and booths, They use Covid 19 procedures, with a very good staff. They have an open kitchen, a street food menu. I am not sure about spelling, I had Tummy Wum, Pat Ty.

title: Ayesha Lebanese
text: Ayesha has a Mediterranean decor, they use Covid 19 procedures, parking, very good staff. Their customers are mainly middle aged locals. I enjoyed catch of the day.

title: Dunkin'
text: Dunkin' is fantastic coffee, great menu, very good staff . Its Covid 19 procedures, parking, great location.

title: Keewaydin Island
text: Keewaydin Island is just beautiful white sand, very clean. You need to bring your own drinks, or they have food boats. You can use your own boat, or the shuttle. It's a day trip.

title: French Cafe
text: Bonjour has a French decor, its small, very good staff. Coffee is pretty good, especially with the deserts.

title: White Powder
text: Siesta Beach has a great crew, very clean, the beach is very grand with white powder for sand. Most of the visitors are locals, male and female, ages from parents with children, teenagers and grandparents. They have all the sea sports and activities.

title: Crooked Snook
text: Crooked Snook is Tiki Bar @ South Seas Island Resort. Covid 19 procedures, great staff. We enjoyed a couple of rum punch cocktails.

title: Harbourside Bar & Grill
text: Harbourside is at South Season Island Resort, the 330 acre resort is 1/3 of the Northern tip of the 6 mile long island. Its elegant but dress is family casual. They are Covid 19, a very good staff, and menu. We enjoyed the seafood special.

title: Zeugma Mediterranean
text: Zeugma's is practicing Covid 19 procedures, has a good staff. The decor was Turkish, the customers were mainly locals, about evenly split male and female in their 50's. I had Ice Tea, a smoked eggplant, desert.

title: Los Bocados
text: It's new, doing Covid 19 procedures, parking, a good staff. I saw the TV episode, "Dinners, Dive-Ins, & Dives". South Florida has a lot of Mexican Restaurants, here the pitch is 'build your own burrito'. I had Ice Tea and built a citrus pork quesadilla.

title: Delray Beach Market
text: Florida's largest food hall has 4 stories, with 27 vendors. That's 150,000 sq. ft. of places to eat. Everything is Covid 19 procedures, very good staff, unbelievable menu. I enjoyed my meal. The only thing I didn't like was Gov. Ron DeSantis not wearing a mask.

title: Flanigan's Bar & Grill
text: Flanigan's has a very good staff, Covid 19 procedures, parking, great menu. I enjoyed ice tea and cobb salad.

title: Denny's
text: Denny's has a very good staff, the facility is Covid 19 procedure compliant. They have a good menu, for breakfast I usually have the superslam and coffee.

title: Quore Gelato
text: Touting flavors like ricotta fig, Cognac, dulce de leche, and tequila, this boozy scoop shop has customers of all ages. It's major customers are locals and guests of the Hotel 'the Costa Hollywood Beach Resort'.

title: Planta South Beach
text: Planta South Beach is Covid 19 procedures, has a great staff. Planta showcases all vegan plant based versions of comfort food. I had a sushi platter, all the fish is made from plant based fish substitutes.

title: Dyan's Country Kitchen
text: Dyan's Country Kitchen doing a very good job with Covid 19 procedures, the staff was short handed. The menu and food was good, but the coffee is sub par.

title: Dandee Donuts
text: Dandee Donuts is doing Covid 19 procedures, parking, great staff, good menu, coffee. But they have the best donuts. Their customers are mainly locals, their ages depend on the time of day, 20's & 40's on the way to work; as many fathers with children as mothers.

title: Breezes
text: Breezes located at the Bahia Mar has an elegant decor, great staff, menu or buffet. We both enjoyed the buffet.

title: Casa Sensei
text: Casa Sensei following Covid 19 procedures, good staff, Asian/Latin fusion menu. Nice decor, enjoyed experience.

title: Subway
text: Subway is clean, great menu, good staff, facilities. I enjoyed footlong sandwich, chips, coffee, cookie.

title: Grand Isle State Park
text: Grand Isle is very picturesque, and people love to camp here. I am not a camper fan, but enjoyed visiting. They have a great pier, camp sites right on the beach, on the Gulf of Mexico, swimming, fishing. You can just watch the dolphins, dive down to the shipwreck, use the observation tower, crabbing, nature trails.

title: Dandee Donut Factory
text: Dandee Donut Factory is Covid 19 procedures good, its comfortable, good staff, coffee. But the reason for their customers are the best donuts in Florida. The customers are mainly locals, equally divided between male & female & children.

title: Dunkin'
text: Following Covid 19 procedures , very good staff. I used the drive through, and had bagel and black coffee.

title: Gemini Springs Park
text: Following Covid 19 procedures, its $6. per car fee, has parking, facilities, picnic, playground, swimming, rentals (kayak). Customers mainly couples in 30's w/children.

title: Winter Estates Edison & Ford
text: The Estates are next door to each other, lovely grounds, beautiful houses (now museums). They are Covid 19 procedure, you can get lost in your thoughts with your tour.

title: McDonald's
text: McDonald's doing a good job with Covid 19 procedures, Good staff, facilities, parking. I enjoyed sausage egg & cheese, black coffee.

title: Ichetucknee Springs State Park
text: Ichetucknee Springs State Park has 2241 acres, Covid 19 procedures, facilities. Lots of things to do, rivers, swim, snorkel, fish. The trails are well maintained, by very good staff.

title: Lester's
text: Lester's is local chain, they started in 1957 on Hwy 84, I have eaten @ all 4 locations, this one on Coconut Creek is closest to my home. They follow Covid 19 procedures, very good staff, parking. Susan & I enjoyed breakfast w/coffee.

title: Denny's
text: Denny's Key West is following Covid 19 procedures, great staff, parking, facilities. I enjoyed superslam breakfast and black coffee.

title: Hugh Taylor Birch State Park
text: Hugh Taylor Birch has a very good staff, parking, facilities, Covid 19 procedures. It's on the Intracoastal with all the things to do. You have hiking trails, beach, wildlife ( lots of squirrels), birds.

title: Marie Selby Botanical Gardens
text: Marie Selby Botanical Gardens are just beautiful, the staff does a wonderful job keeping the property Covid 19 clean and the plants in great condition. The visitors are a majority local, older, mixed about half male and female. I enjoyed the Bromeliad.

title: Crema Gourmet Espresso
text: Crema exudes European chic, with a minimalist black and white color scheme, chandeliers and a large, marble espresso bar. Outside is covered seating, on the 2,000 sq. ft. tree lined patio. Lots of parking, Covid 19 procedures, great staff, great menu. Customers about 95% local, maybe equal mix male, female, 10% older, 10% children. Lots of latte's being served, Susan had one, I enjoyed black coffee.

title: Homosassa Springs State Park
text: This is a beautiful park with a great staff, facilities, kept clean. Visitors are a lot of locals, maybe 35% tourists, probably 1/3 male, 1/3 female and 1/3 children. Manatees are around, and fish, birds, wildlife. You can swim, fish. They have trails and a zoo.
place: Ellie Schiller Homosassa Springs Wildlife State Park

title: Bonefish Grill
text: Bonefish Grill is one of our favorites, great staff, clean, great food. For Easter they offered bundles too go, we picked up two: salmon and chicken. Perfect.

title: Ann's Snack Bar
text: Ann's Snack Bar stared in 1971, its very small, the decor has no frills but its clean. She has customers that wait in line, most are locals, middle aged, equally split male and female. She has a food counter with a few stools and a few booths. Its not about beer or bar food, its a hamburger snack bar; voted (Ghetto Burger) America's Best

title: Tosohatchee State Park
text: Tosohatchee doesn't have a lot of parking, lots of trees, visitors mainly middle aged locals driving over to the space coast. They have wildlife.

title: Charles H, Bronson State Forest
text: Christmas, Fl. is east of Orlando, its clean, facilities, parking, and lots of trees. They have a hiking trail, you can ride a bike. They have birds and wildlife, very few people. I have mailed cards @ Christmas from Christmas.

title: Edward Ball Wakulla Springs State Park
text: The park has flora and fona, and the birds and wildlife as well. I saw more alligators than seminoles although I was a lot closer to Florida State. They have boats and lots of things to do.
place: Edward Ball Wakulla Springs State Park

title: McDonald's
text: They have a good staff, facilities, parking ,clean, I had a breakfast sandwich and black coffee. The price was good.

title: Dunkin'
text: It's national chain, facilities, clean. We got sandwich, and black coffee, we enjoyed our experience.

title: Lettuce Lake
text: It's a regional park, you pay $2. per car; it has facilities, clean, pet ok. They have the lake, alligators, birds and wildlife.

title: OBC Kitchen
text: OBC Kitchen is very clean, doing what's expected, nice decor. They have very good staff, unexpected menu. Customers are 90% local most in their 50's.

title: Beaver's
text: Beaver's is clean, good staff, very popular, parking, menu only locals understand. The decor is western, has booths, wooden tables, the customers are 95% local, split equally male & female, ages 25 to 65. They like bar food. A Nock Up is a sandwich, that an a chicken fried steak w/egg on top are popular.

title: Grand Depot Cafe
text: Grand Depot was rustic with Grand Canyon decor. The have a very clean restaurant, good facilities, parking. country menu, good coffee.

title: Bearizona Wildlife Park
text: The park is wonderful, most of the animals are abandon as babies unable to return to the wild. I was able to see the staff feed many different animals. They have bears, wolfs, deer, one moose, donkey and bobcats.

title: Subway
text: Subway has a good staff, facilities, clean. parking. We both had unsweet tea (she had sweet & low). We got 6 inch special, w/chips.

title: Delnor Wiggins Pass State Park
text: Delnor Wiggins Pass is a very good park, good staff, clean, parking, facilities. It has beautiful white sand, shells, trails, restaurants near, things to do. They have birds, wildlife, the people are 80% local ages children to seniors.

title: Highlands Hammock State Park
text: Highlands Hammock is 900,000 acres in Sebring, lots of flora and the hammock is the star. The staff does great keeping the park clean as well as the facilities. Parking, visitor center, well marked trails, biking, birds and wildlife.

title: Dunkin;
text: Dunkin' is one of my favorite early morning stops. They have a great staff, its clean, facilities. I had a bagel and black coffee.

title: Dunkin'
text: Dunkin' a great chain, clean facilities, very good staff. I love the coffee also had toasted bagel and cream cheese.

title: Subway
text: Subway national chain, parking, very clean, great fast menu. They have a very good staff. I got the $6. special (chicken sandwich, chips, sprite).

title: Little Talot Island State Park
text: You can walk from Big Talbot to Little Talbot. Little Talbot has 5 miles of undeveloped beach, being on the East Coast the sand is brown to gray, hard packed, flees. But that's a lot of beach to swim, fish. It has a sand bar that brakes the waves so you can see the fish come in. They have birds and wildlife.

title: John Pennekamp Coral Reef State Park
text: The Coral Reef is being restored, lots of people want to help. You can scuba and snorkel in the area. On top you can swim, kayak. There is a mangrove forest area.
place: John Pennekamp Coral Reef State Park

title: Sarasota Jungle Gardens
text: Its 10 acres of plants, trails, birds, and wildlife. They have a great staff, its clean, parking, gift shop, children seem to be having most fun. People are mainly from Florida in their 40,s with children in tow.

title: Bok Tower Gardens
text: Bok Tower Gardens was a visit with family and friends. The park is just wonderful, especially in the spring everything is blooming, azaleas on every trail. They have an entrance fee, its minimal.

title: Dunkin'
text: Dunkin' is a very good chain. They have a good staff. I[ts very clean. They have my favorite black coffee.

title: Lake Louisa State Park
text: Lake Louise offers lots to do on the water, swimming, canoeing, fishing. They have a very good staff, the facilities are clean. They have birds, wildlife, and horses. You can go horseback riding.

title: Lake Eola Park
text: Lake Eola Park is a park you can take the kids, they have lease laws but dogs are also welcome. Its very clean, benches, facilities, sculptures, birds. The wildlife is more rabbits and squirrels.

title: Dunkin'
text: Dunkin' one of my favorite morning drive through's when on a trip. They are clean, very good staff, love their coffee and had a glazed cake stick donut.

title: Myakka River State Park
text: Myakka River State Park is a wonderful experience, its really Florida at its natural. Wonderful flora and fauna, you can picnic, bike, hike, see real interesting birds, like the wading birds. Wildlife like alligators, pigs that are wild after generations in the park.

title: Clam Pass Park
text: They have a boardwalk through the mangrove. You can see wildlife in the coastal habitat. The beach is beautiful white sand, clean, facilities.

title: Keating Beach
text: Keating Beach is mainly frequented by locals, teenagers to young families. You can swim, fish. You need to travel for facilities.

title: Anne Kolb Nature Center
text: Anne Kolb Nature Center is clean has a very good staff doing good work for the everglades. The scenery is great, trails, water, birds, wildlife.

title: Lake Seminole Park
text: The park is secluded, has facilities, you can fish, hike. There is wildlife, rabbits, squirrels and lots of birds.

title: Cayo Costa State Park
text: If you are in Captiva and a very good swimmer you are almost here. If you want to look for shells this will seem like paradise. The beach is super, you can fish, swim, hike.

title: Chez Marie
text: It's been a while, but the decor and ambiance are lovely. The staff is doing a super job with Covid 19 procedures. We both had wine, Susan had a shrimp cocktail, fillet and lavender creme brulee. I enjoyed house salad and salmon and French onion soup.

title: Caladesi Island
text: They have beautiful beaches, Covid 19 clean facilities. You can swim, fish, kayaking. Its a small island but there are lots of birds, wildlife, squirrels, tortoises & armadillos.

title: Olive Garden
text: This is a regular stop for Susan & I, the decor is Italian. They have a great staff, doing a super job with Covid 19 procedures. Our normal order is soup & salad, ice tea. We also got 2 of the $5 to go meals.

title: St. Augustine Alligator Farm
text: They have lots of alligator, maybe 800 or more, and its a zoo. It was probably wrong but I saw something that said they have 233 species of crocks, Are there that many species? The customers are a lot of locals with their children, and tourist with their children, and baby alligators getting their picture taken with children.
place: St. Augustine Alligator Farm Zoological Park

title: Times Square Ft Myers
text: They have facilities, restaurants, things to do and see in Times Square. Ft Myers is doing a very good job keeping it clean.

title: Fountain of Youth
text: Archaeological Park very educational and fascinating, people in period dress. Covid 19 procedures followed. Things to do, facilities, restaurants.

title: Harbor Walk Marina
text: It's downtown, mainly smaller boats, restaurants, things to do. People with boats are in their 50's about half locals, younger people are working on boats.
